	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Hagerstown</placeName> <date>April 16&#47;63</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I take the liberty to address<lb/> to you these few lines to inform in regard to<lb/> the proceedings of a certain gentleman named<lb/> &#8220;<persName>Rabbi Holstein</persName>&#8221; whom you gave a good<lb/> <sic>reccomendation</sic> as a man who would &#38; could<lb/> with integrity fill the office of a Schoet &#38;<lb/> Hassan&#44; but I am sorry to say you were greatly<lb/> mistaken in your man as you will hear from<lb/> the following facts which I hope you will place<lb/> in a <sic>conspicous</sic> part of your much valuable<lb/> Paper&#44; the &#8220;Occident&#8221; for it is a disgrace to the<lb/> Jewish name.  <persName>Mr Holstein</persName> came here last<lb/> <date>January</date> with his family with letters of<lb/> <sic>reccomendation</sic> from <persName>Rev Dr Raphel</persName> of <placeName>New<lb/> York</placeName> &#38; <persName>Rev I. Leeser</persName> of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> as a<lb/> man capable to instruct the children of<lb/> this town in various forms &#38; rites of the<lb/> Jewish Religion &#38; also to butcher for the<lb/> Jewish families of this town so that could<lb/> live like true Israelites&#44; but the disgraced his<lb/> office in the following manner.  First he<lb/> persuaded a certain man here a butcher &#38; a<lb/> <persName>Jehuda</persName> to leave his wife &#38; children&#44; &#38; at last<lb/> had so much power over this man that he</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>left his wife &#38; children to want &#38; he &#40;<lb/> <persName>Mr Holstein</persName>&#41; went in partnership with<lb/> this butcher &#38; did not send to his business<lb/> at all for which he came for.  He did not<lb/> teach the children would not butcher as a &#40;Schoet&#41;<lb/> ought to have done&#41; for an Israelite&#59; also on a<lb/> <date>Sabbath</date> he smoked&#44; butchered became beastly<lb/> drunk&#44; &#38; tried more than once to drive the<lb/> poor woman &#40;whom he had ruined already by<lb/> depriving the mother of a husband &#38; the<lb/> children of a father&#41; in the street &#38; insulting<lb/> her in every manner possible that he made himself<lb/> so obnoxious that the children of this town<lb/> both Jews &#38; Christians stare at him when they<lb/> saw him  <persName>Mrs Stein</persName> the forsaken woman with<lb/> her children moved in a house which was<lb/> bought by her husband &#38; <persName>Mr Holstein</persName> bought<lb/> the house from her husband so that he<lb/> could drive the poor suffering soul out into<lb/> the street but he did not succeed as well as he<lb/> expected for by breaking the peace so often &#38;c<lb/> the law was on her side &#38; at last he was<lb/> arrested with <persName>Mr Stein</persName> &#38; placed in jail where<lb/> thanks be to the Almighty he will stay there<lb/> but in my opinion he ought to rot there his<lb/> lifetime.  Being advised by the leading<lb/> Israelites to write the above facts so that the<lb/> whole world should know it &#38; so take caution<lb/> Hoping that you will correct all mistakes</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>and send me the &#8220;Occident&#8221; in which you will<lb/> place it I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Your obedient Serv&#39;t</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Jacob J. Greenewald</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Son of <persName>Mr Greeenewald</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">of the firm <persName>Greenewald &#38;<lb/>Kohlberg</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><placeName>No 110 N. Third</placeName></p>
				<p>Please excuse</p>
				<p>mistakes &#38; bad writing</p>
				<p>N. B. Give the above to <persName>Dr Wise</persName> of <placeName><sic>Cincinatti</sic></placeName><lb/> so that he can place in public print<lb/> Yours <persName role="author">JJG</persName>.</p>
